# Code Review Standards

**Format when flagging**:
```
CRITICAL: [issue] - [impact] - [fix]
WARNING: [issue] - [suggestion]
```

**Checklist**: Type safety (Any, missing hints). Security (injection, secrets, validation). Performance (N+1, blocking I/O). Architecture (god modules, coupling). Error handling (specific raise/error types, narrow catch, chained causes — flag generic `Exception` / `except Exception:` / ignored Go `err`). Tests (edge cases, error paths, `pytest.raises` / `errors.Is`). Duplication / reinvention (new code mirroring existing module without extending → WARNING unless justified). Reuse security (extend module/dep with unresolved CRITICAL CVE or obvious unsafe API → CRITICAL; HIGH CVE without stated mitigation or new dep without audit mention → WARNING). Include code snippet for fix when suggesting change.
